txt.en: 'I am Mablung, and my companion is Damrod. We are Rangers of Ithilien.'
'We are descended from a long line of folk who called these woods home, and Steward Denethor has charged us with its protection.'
'We seldom roam this far within, but today we come to ambush the evil Men from Harad.'
'But we do not sit idle. The Southrons march brazenly and heedlessly upon our own roads to swell the hosts of Mordor.'
Instance: Halflings and Oliphaunts
'They shall not pass unchallenged... not while Faramir leads our host.'
'His life seems charmed, as if fate spares him for some greater end.'
'Sleep while you are able.'
'If the Captain returns, he will want to depart swiftly. The Enemy will pursue us when the news reaches him.'
'I doubt the Captain will leave you unattended in the woods, Master Samwise, but we shall see.'
'It sounds like the smithying of a thousand blacksmiths all together! This is as near as I should like them to get.'
'An Oliphaunt! So they exist, and I have gotten to see one. What a tale!'
'Well, no one shall believe me if I tell them.'
'Phew. If that's all over and done, I think I'll have a sleep.'
'Curse the Haradrim! They are under the sway of the Enemy. Alas, I fear that Gondor will fall.'
'Go quietly when you leave! No need to disturb me.'
'His strength and malice have grown great indeed, and there is little hope for Minas Tirith.'
'They are coming! They have broken through the trap, and our Captain pursues!'
'Mûmak! Mûmak! May the Valar save us and turn his path!'
'What are your names, and where are you from?'
